T1  - On the evaluation of poly-t density functions
AU  - Richard, J.-F.
AU  - Tompa, H.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 12
IS  - 3
SP  - 335
EP  - 351
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/04/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(80)90060-3
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407680900603
AB  - Poly-t densities are defined by the property that their kernel is a product, or a ratio of products, of multivariate t-density kernels. As discussed in Drèze (1977), these densities arise as Bayesian posterior densities for regression coefficients under a variety of specifications for the prior density and the data generating process. We have therefore developed methods and computer algorithms to evaluate integrating constants and other characteristics of poly-t densities with no more than a single quadratic form in the numerator (section 2). As a by-product of our analysis we have also derived an algorithm for the computation of moments of positive definite quadratic forms in Normal variables (section 3). In section 4 we discuss inference on the sampling variances associated with the models discussed in Drèze (1977).
ER  - 

